nodes.bodyText:
@abollini : Tests for reloading configs exist in the dspace-services layer.  Here's the one that tests for an automatic reload. There's others in this same Test class that test other areas of configuration reload/population, etc. https://github.com/DSpace/DSpace/blob/master/dspace-services/src/test/java/org/dspace/servicemanager/config/DSpaceConfigurationServiceTest.java#L529
I still have a strong preference for avoiding any static references to beans/classes.  It's really unnecessary here, since you can get a reference via the DSpaceServicesFactory rather than re-caching it locally.
That said, I'll let it slide here since you've added tests to prove that it works as expected, regardless of the static reference.

Here's where you could just replace this line with:
return DSpaceServicesFactory.getInstance().getConfigurationService().getBooleanProperty("core.authorization.community-admin.group", true);
This same replacement will work for all the static methods in this class.

